<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Geochronology/Division> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/description> "Geological time is divided into useful segments that are then further sub-divided. A well known example is the Jurassic, which is a Period, part of the (much longer) Mezosoic Era. The Jurassic Period is sub-divided into the Early, Mid and Late Jurassic Epochs. Some Eras are divided into sub-eras, similarly, Periods, Epochs and Ages can have sub-divisions."@en .
<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Geochronology/Division> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/identifier> "http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Geochronology/Division"@en .
