<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/ref/Geochronology/Rank> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/description> "Geologists label divisions of geological time with named ranks which indicate which level of the hierarchy of terms they belong to. The preferred labels in this scheme are the chronological rank names; the equivalent stratigraphical rank name is provided as an alternative label."@en .
